Subject: [PATCH 0/2] drm/panel: himax-hx83112a: add Vsmart Active 1 DJN
 1080x2160 variant

This adds support for the DJN HX83112A 1080x2160 panel on the Vsmart
Active 1 (PQ6001, a rebrand of the BQ Aquaris X2 Pro, LineageOS codename
zangyapro), by extending the existing panel-himax-hx83112a driver (so far
Fairphone 3 only) into a multi-variant driver.

The Fairphone 3 variant (djn,9a-3r063-1102b) is kept byte-for-byte. The
new djn,a1-hx83112a variant differs in mode (1080x2160) and, notably, in
init: it issues only exit-sleep + display-on and does not pulse reset.

This is deliberate and matches the hardware design. The bootloader
performs the full HX83112A register init for this TDDI panel, and the
downstream vendor kernel device tree confirms it: it ships the same
minimal on-command (exit-sleep + display-on only) for this panel and its
HX83112A siblings (the DJN, Truly and DJN11 variants), with no register
programming exposed in any DT. Pulsing reset would wipe that init, so the
variant leaves the reset line deasserted. I was not able to obtain a
standalone init sequence from the vendor; if you would prefer the driver
to self-initialise, I am happy to discuss the options.

Tested on hardware (v6.19.x, postmarketOS): the panel comes up through the
DPU + DSI + panel pipeline at 1080x2160, the backlight responds and the
GPU (freedreno) works.

The device tree for the board and its qcom.yaml board compatible are not
part of this series; they will follow via the qcom / arm-soc tree once the
binding and driver have landed.

